<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-11-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="417" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6369/268.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San
                                    Jose</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-11-11"><hi rend="italic">November 11,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Merry says that Nicaraguan Army while fighting revolutionists
                            offensively invaded Costa Rica on the southern bank of San Juan River,
                            and that Costa Rica had asked explanation from Managua.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>